Dragon Boat

Making a spectacle at Burning Man still needs to make sense, so building a Dragon Boat seemed logical. The only creature able to survive a barren lake basin would, naturally, be a dragon. Six months, 40 hours and one giant papier-mâché dragon head later, the Dragon Boat was born. Hand-painted, hand-crafted and handled completely from scratch, the Dragon Boat is a reminder of the brilliance of adaptability. 
The making of Dragon Boat
